    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-04T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="695"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/609e</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-04T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6162. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 418. Repeat the following to Berne. We have advised <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_OF1">Oederlin</persName> that we will postpone
                    discussion of the proposed extension of the Swiss agreement until the arrival of
                    Doctor <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SH1">Sulzer</persName>. <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SH1">Sulzer</persName> is expected here
                    momentarily. We will cable you further.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
